Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.39,0:00:18.36,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.64,0:00:29.82,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.07,0:00:36.75,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:47.88,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.13,0:00:56.81,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.09,0:01:08.70,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.98,0:01:20.59,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.87,0:01:26.43,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.71,0:01:36.23,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.98,0:02:01.18,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(385,350)}Ep. 33 - A Lost Dream
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.00,0:02:24.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Three long years have passed\Nsince we arrived to Southern Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.08,0:02:36.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In that time, from a small settlement with measly 300 inhabitants, Adelaide transformed into a bustling city.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.11,0:02:39.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, also with a splendid bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.60,0:02:41.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,October 1840.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.90,0:02:48.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought that we could see it from here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.34,0:02:49.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.20,0:02:50.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Our house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.71,0:02:51.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.72,0:02:54.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The house where we used to live before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:59.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No way you could see it from here.\NThe river meanders a lot, plus tons of trees.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:01.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But... It's that way, right, Kate?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.90,0:03:03.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. That way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.39,0:03:04.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.49,0:03:09.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Say, you wanna go look at that house?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.56,0:03:10.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.32,0:03:12.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've also haven't seen Doctor Deighton in ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.80,0:03:13.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.13,0:03:17.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, Little. Enough waiting. Let's go now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.70,0:03:25.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,About year or so ago,\Nwe left our old house upstream the river
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.49,0:03:30.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,and moved into this house on Angas Street. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.59,0:03:48.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going, Tob?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.79,0:03:50.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To go play look for the sisters. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.00,0:03:53.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Kate and Lucy should return soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.97,0:03:56.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So you'd also better not to stray too far.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.41,0:03:57.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I won't go far.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.98,0:03:59.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look out for the carriages!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.51,0:04:00.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.61,0:04:12.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you two! Been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.61,0:04:14.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bernard!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.11,0:04:18.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought you guys no longer live in this area. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.10,0:04:21.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We went to see the opening ceremony\Nof the Adelaide bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.03,0:04:26.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When we looked this way while standing on the bridge,\Nwe became so, oh, so nostalgic!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.10,0:04:27.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.11,0:04:28.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Fancy a ride?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.12,0:04:30.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.12,0:04:30.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.11,0:04:34.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... You have Little with you?\NWe can't take Little along...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.42,0:04:36.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. Little would be running after us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.88,0:04:39.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, get in, then.\NAlthough it's a little tight up here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.61,0:04:39.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.86,0:04:43.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,May I add, you two have sure grown quite big.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.29,0:04:51.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is this your carriage, Mr. Bernard?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.49,0:04:54.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible! I'm nowhere near rich enough\Nfor such purchases.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.90,0:04:57.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,This is the carriage,\Nallocated to the Surveyor General.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:04:59.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, so it's Colonel Light's carriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.51,0:05:00.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well aren't you a dunce?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.79,0:05:01.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.69,0:05:04.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel Light passed away last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.38,0:05:05.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.79,0:05:10.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Right now, Charles Sturt is the Surveyor General.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.19,0:05:12.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And I serve as his personal secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.33,0:05:14.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so that's how it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.02,0:05:15.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Admirable growth, Mr. Bernard! 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.21,0:05:19.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't exactly say a secretary job\Nis all that admirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.20,0:05:21.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.35,0:05:27.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Looks like Mr. Pettywell\Nis moving out of his house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.85,0:05:30.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, it's heavy... Hey, watch where you step!
Comment: 0,0:05:30.99,0:05:33.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.69,0:05:39.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll just quickly grab some things,\Nthen return to the office at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.62,0:05:40.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.94,0:05:44.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then, you'll be able to take us\Nto King William Street, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.89,0:05:46.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.16,0:05:49.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But remember, I'll be leaving again\Nin 20 minutes or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:53.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. We only came to say hello to Doctor Deighton.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.41,0:05:56.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.50,0:06:01.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with Little?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.49,0:06:02.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.89,0:06:05.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.29,0:06:13.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So Mr. Pettywell now keeps a bulldog?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:15.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looks strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.12,0:06:18.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I bet, he went to the trouble\Nof bringing it all the way from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.00,0:06:25.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's a no-go! You can't be\Nmaking enemies with that dog as well, Little.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.70,0:06:27.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.30,0:06:41.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And where is Mr. Pettywell's new residence? 
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.30,0:06:43.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? That's be on Angas Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.02,0:06:44.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Angas Street?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.23,0:06:47.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh... Thanks for telling me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.48,0:06:50.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy! Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.19,0:06:52.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't believe it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.79,0:06:55.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell is moving to a house on Angas Street!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.68,0:06:56.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.60,0:06:58.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But how in the world...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:07:02.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe he's moving to a house next to us again!\NJeez, that Mr. Pettywell...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.27,0:07:06.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It ain't gonna be pretty. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.10,0:07:10.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem like anyone lives there,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.09,0:07:13.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Pretty sure we sold it to some Mr. Watson. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.80,0:07:27.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, no one lives here.\NLook how dilapidated it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.00,0:07:29.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, exactly so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.40,0:07:34.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,For the last three months, not a soul lived here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.01,0:07:36.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor Deighton!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:40.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, I'll suffocate if you keep pushing so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.70,0:07:43.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning! It's been a truly long time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.69,0:07:49.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I wasn't looking for a split second,\Nbut you two have grown so big already!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.30,0:07:50.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.95,0:07:55.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Little, I see you're doing fine as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.09,0:07:57.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But why isn't anyone living here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.71,0:08:01.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because Mr. Watson sold the house and the plot\Nand went to live in the city of Gawler. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.96,0:08:04.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But why doesn't the buyer live here either?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.44,0:08:07.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell bought up this whole stretch of land. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.40,0:08:10.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell bought it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.97,0:08:17.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I hear his plan is to subdivide the land\Ninto smaller lots, build houses on them, and sell.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.21,0:08:20.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know the land is rapidly growing in value?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.56,0:08:25.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We know. That's why our dad\Nhad already given up on buying any farmland. 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.69,0:08:27.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.01,0:08:30.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Both the farmlands\Nand the residential areas grew in price.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.50,0:08:34.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Pettywell also operates\Nunder the assumption the price will keep rising.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.20,0:08:35.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, but then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.93,0:08:36.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.83,0:08:41.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If all the land here now belongs to Mr. Pettywell,\Nwhat'll become of that house of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.90,0:08:44.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.34,0:08:49.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, doesn't you house\Nnow technically stand on Mr. Pettywell's estate?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.19,0:08:52.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he demands that I move out these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.08,0:08:54.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're getting evicted, Doctor? 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.79,0:08:57.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not goin' anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.51,0:09:01.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I came to really like this house your dad built.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.81,0:09:04.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Come fire and brimstone,\NI'm not goin' anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.22,0:09:07.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You heard me right!\NAin't no way I'm moving out!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.00,0:09:14.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. In these past two years,\NAdelaide underwent a brilliant transformation. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.81,0:09:17.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But that also means\Nthere's more nasty stuff happening. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.46,0:09:20.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what dad told us -\Nbad people became numerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.79,0:09:24.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But the police cells became even more numerous. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.38,0:09:27.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we keep hiring new policemen,\Nand it's getting troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.60,0:09:30.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There are folk like Mr. Pettywell,\Nstill enjoying hefty profits,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.90,0:09:34.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but there's much more of those\Nwho came all the way to Southern Australia
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:38.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,just to have their dreams smashed\Nand end up living hand-to-mouth. 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.01,0:09:41.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's not what's gonna happen\Nto our family, right, sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.54,0:09:43.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows. We aren't exactly wealthy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.90,0:09:45.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's very different from your case!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.80,0:09:48.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you have such a splendid house, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.37,0:09:50.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Also with a small field and orchard in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.61,0:09:54.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not nearly enough\Nto be selling vegetables and fruits to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.07,0:09:57.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, doesn't your family have\NClara and Ben who are also working?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.00,0:09:59.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even so, dad can barely find any work. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.21,0:10:01.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.50,0:10:04.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's 'cause your father\Nhad been a farmer for all his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.92,0:10:07.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,His experience at cultivating fields\Nand keeping livestock
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.69,0:10:12.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be converted into some useful skill\Nfor quarrying or building roads. 
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.59,0:10:15.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If only Mr. Pettywell didn't snatch it from us,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.09,0:10:19.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,we'd have ourselves a marvelous farm by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.50,0:10:27.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So? How about on this corner?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.44,0:10:29.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.51,0:10:31.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Give my greetings to your dad and mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.45,0:10:32.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.79,0:10:34.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are careful on your way home, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.99,0:10:38.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to stop at Mrs. Mac's store\Non the way to buy some bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.39,0:10:40.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Want us to tell something to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.71,0:10:42.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.79,0:10:45.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell her that I'll also stop by soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.30,0:10:46.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.02,0:10:48.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, and also, say hello to Clara. Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.59,0:10:58.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Are you alright? Not tired or anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.43,0:11:04.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You never question Little's infinite energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.81,0:11:06.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.44,0:11:07.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.30,0:11:31.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:36.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.14,0:11:37.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Give me just a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.90,0:11:41.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Lucy! Leave the dog outside, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.70,0:11:50.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Mrs. Mac?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.07,0:11:50.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.91,0:11:51.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.09,0:11:58.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.40,0:12:00.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Kate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.29,0:12:02.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We saw Mr. Bernard just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.71,0:12:04.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting. Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.21,0:12:05.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Near our previous house.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.51,0:12:09.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What were you doing all the way out there? 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.03,0:12:10.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Remembering the old times. 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.44,0:12:13.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was also feeling lonely there,\Nnow that you're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.20,0:12:27.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It smells wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.75,0:12:29.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need something else from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.56,0:12:33.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Bernard said he'd pay you a visit before long.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.15,0:12:35.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Bernard's "before long" could mean anything. 
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.01,0:12:42.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, but thanks for telling me either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.40,0:12:44.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can get your usual bread from Clara.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.31,0:12:46.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.70,0:12:47.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry for the delay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.30,0:12:51.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your purchase!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.40,0:13:00.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to have our usual bread, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.80,0:13:01.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.28,0:13:07.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We've been to the opening ceremony\Nof the Adelaide Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.20,0:13:08.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Was it very crowded?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.42,0:13:09.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.21,0:13:11.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, what do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.86,0:13:13.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.07,0:13:16.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Me and John are going to see the play tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.44,0:13:17.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What play?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.10,0:13:19.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Romeo and Juliet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.60,0:13:24.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The Liverpool Theater troupe\Ncame from England to stage it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.54,0:13:25.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wanna see it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.84,0:13:28.16,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're still a child, so it's out of question.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.40,0:13:33.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The problem I have is...\NWhat do you think dad will say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.20,0:13:35.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He'll probably forbid you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.26,0:13:38.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"Watching plays is highly depraved of a maiden..." 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.52,0:13:40.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad has such a stuffy predisposition. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.71,0:13:42.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But that's such a backward thinking. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.98,0:13:43.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.50,0:13:47.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, dad had been so insusceptible lately. 
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.49,0:13:50.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister! John's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.68,0:13:53.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What was he thinking?\NIt's still too soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.51,0:13:55.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's also dressed to the nines!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.11,0:14:01.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! He looks very determined too, our John! 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.83,0:14:03.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.91,0:14:06.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey-hey, that's quite the welcome. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.08,0:14:10.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John, you've finished the work already?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:11.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.62,0:14:14.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm still far from being done.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.21,0:14:15.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.41,0:14:20.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in any case, I'm ready and waiting,\Nso I thought I'd stop by to let you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.65,0:14:21.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Looking sharp, John.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.85,0:14:23.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.09,0:14:26.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Working as a carpenter means\Nyou have plenty of free time, I imagine. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.30,0:14:28.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It was a special kind of work today. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.60,0:14:37.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It almost feels unreal. 
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.30,0:14:38.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.30,0:14:42.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They've built a theater in Adelaide\Nand are now staging plays there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.61,0:14:45.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Romeo and Juliet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.15,0:14:49.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of play\Ndo you think Romeo and Juliet is?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.26,0:14:52.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm at a loss for words...\NYou don't even know the story of Romeo and Juliet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.70,0:14:53.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.80,0:14:55.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A famous playwright Shake...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.62,0:15:00.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Shakes... No, wait, not Shakepear either.\NShake sounds right. Shake...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.39,0:15:01.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's Shakespeare.
Comment: 0,0:15:01.71,0:15:02.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.91,0:15:04.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.93,0:15:08.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was actually about to say "Shakespeare" myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.39,0:15:09.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that, if so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.89,0:15:14.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Romeo and Juliet is a famous play by Shakespeare.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.40,0:15:16.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand now, Lucy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.07,0:15:17.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I understood really well!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.77,0:15:21.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which,\Nwhat are you two doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.11,0:15:24.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just made a detour on our way home.\NWhat about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.55,0:15:27.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Going home from the port.\NI have a day off tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.74,0:15:29.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you walk all the way from the port?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.90,0:15:31.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nope, not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.23,0:15:32.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I took a diligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.95,0:15:36.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's very convenient. Not so long ago,\Nyou'd either have to walk all the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.70,0:15:39.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,or hope that someone\Nwould let you ride their cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.29,0:15:42.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But now, anyone can ride it for just three shillings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.63,0:15:44.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Look, that's the one that brought me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.22,0:15:46.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.32,0:15:53.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.19,0:15:53.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.93,0:15:57.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Had a plenty of passengers today.\NMy horse is worn to a frazzle. 
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.70,0:16:01.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, sure, gimme a moment.\NI'll release you right away. 
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.10,0:16:28.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it isn't Tob over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.90,0:16:33.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right! Whenever he has a free minute,\Nhe comes to see the blacksmith work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.39,0:16:36.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tob!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.06,0:16:41.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing?\NLet's go home now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.73,0:16:43.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.19,0:16:50.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he said.\NMr. Pettywell is moving to Angas Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.40,0:16:51.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.52,0:16:56.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if there's a house on Angas Street\Nbig enough for Mr. Pettywell to move in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.12,0:17:01.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, one house away from us... 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.99,0:17:03.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One house away?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.29,0:17:03.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.40,0:17:05.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! {\i1}That{\i0} house!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.83,0:17:07.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, gotta be that house.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.83,0:17:09.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very cruel irony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.43,0:17:12.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing that Pettywell\Ninvade our neighborhood again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.51,0:17:13.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.96,0:17:15.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta be one...
Comment: 0,0:17:16.51,0:17:17.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.35,0:17:19.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Good, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.21,0:17:20.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it from your side! 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.48,0:17:21.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.18,0:17:23.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And now, heave-ho...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.03,0:17:24.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, give it to me now. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.19,0:17:25.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.31,0:17:27.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alright...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.40,0:17:29.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Damn thing's heavy. 
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.32,0:17:32.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it was exactly as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.08,0:17:34.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's worse, Mr. Pettywell keeps a bulldog now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.80,0:17:35.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.51,0:17:40.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thought it's still in the other house,\NI'm sure it'll try to get Little's back up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.69,0:17:42.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,A carriage is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.90,0:18:05.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little, calm down now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.19,0:18:12.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.95,0:18:15.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Children say they've seen it with their own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.63,0:18:19.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll have to put up\Nwith being around Mr. Pettywell again... 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.85,0:18:23.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, this city of Adelaide is really a tiny one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.30,0:18:24.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.75,0:18:29.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And... Clara actually wanted to ask you for a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.92,0:18:31.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.29,0:18:33.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John also came to ask for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.67,0:18:36.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I told them before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.34,0:18:39.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The time is not ripe for that yet.\NThat's my final ruling. 
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.93,0:18:41.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.08,0:18:41.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.79,0:18:44.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't come to talk about marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.15,0:18:45.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Really? What, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.42,0:18:48.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you hear it from them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.70,0:18:57.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Why can't I go see a play?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.30,0:19:01.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Theater is where they teach children\Nall the wrong things. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.51,0:19:03.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But Clara is no longer a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.82,0:19:05.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,To me, she's a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.09,0:19:12.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't think a play such as Romeo and Juliet\Ncould teach Clara any wrong thing, dad. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.00,0:19:14.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't ask for your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.72,0:19:19.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I really didn't want to ever say this,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.10,0:19:22.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,but your way of thinking\Nis about several centuries too old! 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.26,0:19:23.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Old ways are best ways. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.24,0:19:28.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.39,0:19:33.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You know that to succeed in farming,\None ought to embrace the progressive thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.68,0:19:34.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.98,0:19:37.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When you decided to go to Southern Australia,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.08,0:19:39.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,it was because of that progressive farming
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.07,0:19:41.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,that you wanted to put into practice here, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.50,0:19:43.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.09,0:19:53.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I... I wanted to try out a whole kit and caboodle\Nof my progressive ideas on a plot vast enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.38,0:20:00.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Because the government promised\Nthat it would be possible here, in Southern Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.99,0:20:06.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But without any land on my hands,\Nall this progressive farming ain't worth a zilch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.41,0:20:11.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,With all my heart, I pray that you get to implement your progressive farming, if even just a day sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.80,0:20:15.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But... Right now, well, about that theater play...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.40,0:20:17.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.41,0:20:21.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, for a man employed in inventing\Na new ways of progressive farming,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.57,0:20:26.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,staying always stuffy and old-fashioned\Ntoward a theater play is strange, to say the least.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.10,0:20:27.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That... That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.90,0:20:30.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's right! Exactly so!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.04,0:20:31.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.36,0:20:35.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father... You've always kept proving yourself\Na progressively-thinking man!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.69,0:20:40.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As far as farming is concerned, there's no other man\Nwith thinking quite as progressive as yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.20,0:20:43.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So why shouldn't you think progressively\Ntowards theater too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.59,0:20:46.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ben, that was a very compelling argument!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.01,0:20:50.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, Clara.\NDad will quickly come to see the reason, 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.15,0:20:51.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,because he's a very understanding man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.19,0:20:55.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Go before I changed my mind. 
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.82,0:20:57.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.36,0:21:02.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you so much wanna see that play,\Nthen go and see it right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.33,0:21:04.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.20,0:21:07.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.28,0:21:09.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! That was unbecoming, Clara. 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.25,0:21:10.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John, let's go now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.90,0:21:13.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Popple, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.25,0:21:15.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,John, what time is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.84,0:21:18.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Don't worry. We still have\Nplenty of time until the play.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.61,0:21:19.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go change, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.83,0:21:21.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,OK, I'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.26,0:21:24.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, are you happy with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.20,0:21:27.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Those two sure looked delighted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.43,0:21:31.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think of it,\NClara is already nineteen, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.70,0:21:52.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Soppy! Soppy! 
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.21,0:22:01.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If eventually, Soppy also turns out\Nto be a milk-producing goat, that'd be great! 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.68,0:22:06.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sticky and Pansy are already producing plenty.\NAnd we add to that Soppy...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.29,0:22:09.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother could make enough cheese\Nto start selling it!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.00,0:22:11.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If we get a cow, I'll look after it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.52,0:22:13.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Getting a cow wouldn't be half-bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.94,0:22:15.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Should we ask dad for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.72,0:22:20.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No way, it'll put dad into a fix.\NThe family budget is running low right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.30,0:22:30.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, mom asked you to finish sooner here. 
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.91,0:22:32.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost done.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.20,0:22:35.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What about Clara?\NDid she go to see the play, after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.12,0:22:39.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. In a feat of persuasion,\NI made dad change his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.41,0:22:42.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd think I have all the makings of a lawyer?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.13,0:22:44.23,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's with becoming a doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.51,0:22:48.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I gave up on that one.\NI've turned 15 already. It's too late to start now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.60,0:22:50.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So you're becoming a lawyer?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.35,0:22:53.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows. That seems to be just as difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.30,0:22:57.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And what's wrong with becoming a farmer?\NIt'd be great if you could succeed dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.81,0:22:59.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Being a farmer is alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.59,0:23:03.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But right now, our family has but a zilch of land.\NJust some tiny orchard in the backyard. 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.82,0:23:06.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure we'll get a vast plot one day!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.61,0:23:08.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,First obstacle - money.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.12,0:23:09.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That, we haven't for now. 
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.95,0:23:15.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Second - need the government to deliver\Non their promise and stand handing out cheap land.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.02,0:23:17.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't seem to be happening any time soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.50,0:23:20.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Only if we all work hard as best we can...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.00,0:23:26.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then again, even if I start saving up my pay\Nfrom the port customs, it would still be measly amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.06,0:23:29.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I'm all done here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.01,0:23:31.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm done with mine too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.59,0:23:36.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little! Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.60,0:23:38.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please herd Snowflake to here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.31,0:23:42.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's time to get inside now. Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.81,0:23:49.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,One day, I'm certain,\Nwe'll get out vast plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.14,0:23:53.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And then, we'll build a marvelous farm there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.07,0:23:57.86,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's what our family\Nchooses to believe in to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.49,0:24:08.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When Little follows me to school, the teachers\Ngets the wrong idea and scolds me bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.48,0:24:11.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And when we get home,\Na tragic news await there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.49,0:24:14.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"Little and the School".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.93,0:24:16.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
